  "text": "Hypoxic/ischemic conditions are characterized by reduced oxygen availability and trigger broad physiological alterations leading to cell death. The neuroprotective function of DOR activation has emerged recently, and offers interesting clinical perspectives for hypoxic/ ischemic stress (Chao & Xia, 2010; [CITATION_1] . Beneficial effects of DOR activity deduced from in vivo models of hypoxia and ischemia are summarized in Table 4 .",
